1
00:00:21,606 --> 00:00:24,803
<i>BELLA: I'd never given much thought
to how I would die.</i>

2
00:00:24,876 --> 00:00:27,174
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

3
00:00:33,018 --> 00:00:37,853
<i>But dying in the place of someone I love
seems like a good way to go.</i>

4
00:00:46,464 --> 00:00:48,056
(WINGS FLUTTERING)

5
00:00:50,968 --> 00:00:52,868
<i>(OMINOUS THEME PLAYING)</i>

6
00:01:10,554 --> 00:01:15,062
<i>BELLA: So I can't bring myself to
regret the decision to leave home.</i>

7
00:01:16,460 --> 00:01:18,257
<i>I would miss Phoenix.</i>

8
00:01:20,664 --> 00:01:22,393
<i>I'd miss the heat.</i>

9
00:01:25,668 --> 00:01:28,535
<i>I would miss my loving, erratic,
harebrained mother.</i>

10
00:01:28,605 --> 00:01:29,833
(SOFTLY) Okay.

11
00:01:31,207 --> 00:01:32,765
<i>PHIL: Renee, come on.
BELLA: And her new husband.</i>

12
00:01:32,842 --> 00:01:35,606
Guys, come on. I love you both.
We got a plane to catch.

13
00:01:35,678 --> 00:01:40,274
<i>But they want to go on the road,
so I'm gonna spend some time with my dad,</i>

14
00:01:40,717 --> 00:01:42,981
<i>and this will be a good thing.</i>

15
00:01:44,421 --> 00:01:45,854
<i>I think.</i>

16
00:01:46,723 --> 00:01:49,658
<i>(SINGING) When the thorn bush turns white</i>

17
00:01:49,726 --> 00:01:55,926
<i>That's when I'll come home</i>

18
00:01:55,999 --> 00:02:02,962
<i>I am going out to see what I can sow</i>

19
00:02:05,108 --> 00:02:09,669
<i>And I don't know where I'll go</i>

20
00:02:09,745 --> 00:02:13,044
<i>And I don't know what I'll see</i>

21
00:02:13,115 --> 00:02:14,514
<i>BELLA: In the state of Washington,</i>

22
00:02:14,583 --> 00:02:17,552
<i>under a near constant cover
of clouds and rain,</i>

23
00:02:17,619 --> 00:02:20,019
<i>there's a small town named Forks.</i>

24
00:02:20,088 --> 00:02:24,252
<i>Population, 3, 120 people.</i>

25
00:02:25,727 --> 00:02:27,752
<i>This is where I'm moving.</i>

26
00:02:29,898 --> 00:02:31,627
<i>My dad's Charlie.</i>

27
00:02:32,367 --> 00:02:34,562
<i>He's the chief of police.</i>

28
00:02:35,404 --> 00:02:39,135
<i>Curse the powers that be</i>

29
00:02:41,109 --> 00:02:43,976
<i>Cause all I want is...</i>

30
00:02:44,046 --> 00:02:45,843
Your hair's longer.

31
00:02:48,417 --> 00:02:51,249
I cut it since the last time I saw you.

32
00:02:54,489 --> 00:02:55,820
Guess it grew out again.

33
00:03:04,332 --> 00:03:07,859
<i>BELLA: I used to spend two weeks here
almost every summer,</i>

34
00:03:08,536 --> 00:03:10,436
<i>but it's been years.</i>

35
00:03:25,520 --> 00:03:27,351
I've cleared some shelves off
in the bathroom.

36
00:03:27,488 --> 00:03:29,649
Right. One bathroom.

37
00:03:35,795 --> 00:03:38,127
It's a pretty good work lamp.

38
00:03:39,099 --> 00:03:42,000
The sales lady picked out the bed stuff.

39
00:03:42,068 --> 00:03:44,593
You like purple, right?

40
00:03:44,671 --> 00:03:46,263
Purple's cool.

41
00:03:47,040 --> 00:03:48,405
Thanks.

42
00:03:54,748 --> 00:03:56,010
Okay.

43
00:04:01,054 --> 00:04:04,080
<i>BELLA: One of the best things about Charlie,</i>

44
00:04:04,157 --> 00:04:06,057
<i>he doesn't hover.</i>

45
00:04:09,262 --> 00:04:10,695
(CAR HORN HONKS)

46
00:04:13,567 --> 00:04:15,398
Heard you guys coming
all the way down the road.

47
00:04:15,468 --> 00:04:17,059
Good to see you.

48
00:04:18,871 --> 00:04:21,704
Bella, you remember Billy Black.
- Yeah.

49
00:04:21,774 --> 00:04:25,073
Wow, you're looking good.
- Well, I'm still dancing.

50
00:04:25,344 --> 00:04:27,005
I'm glad you're finally here.

51
00:04:27,079 --> 00:04:29,377
Charlie here hasn't shut up about it
since you told him you were coming.

52
00:04:29,448 --> 00:04:30,472
(CHUCKLES)

53
00:04:30,549 --> 00:04:33,450
All right, keep exaggerating.
I'll roll you into the mud.

54
00:04:33,519 --> 00:04:35,350
After I ram you in the ankles.

55
00:04:35,421 --> 00:04:37,013
CHARLIE: You want to go?
- Yeah.

56
00:04:37,089 --> 00:04:38,317
Bring it.

57
00:04:38,390 --> 00:04:41,325
Hi, I'm Jacob.
- Hey.

58
00:04:41,393 --> 00:04:44,157
We used to make mud pies
when we were little.

59
00:04:44,229 --> 00:04:46,060
Right. No, I remember.

60
00:04:46,131 --> 00:04:47,155
(LAUGHS)

61
00:04:47,232 --> 00:04:49,291
Are they always like this?

62
00:04:49,902 --> 00:04:52,769
It's getting worse with old age.
- Good.

63
00:04:52,838 --> 00:04:54,567
So, what do you think?

64
00:04:55,474 --> 00:04:56,736
Of what?

65
00:04:57,276 --> 00:04:59,709
Your homecoming present.
- This?

66
00:05:00,211 --> 00:05:03,078
Just bought it off Billy here.
- Yep.

67
00:05:03,147 --> 00:05:06,173
I totally rebuilt the engine for you.
- Come on.

68
00:05:06,250 --> 00:05:08,013
Oh, my gosh!

69
00:05:08,987 --> 00:05:10,454
This is perfect. Are you joking me?

70
00:05:10,521 --> 00:05:11,783
(JACOB GRUNTS)

71
00:05:11,856 --> 00:05:13,255
Sorry.

72
00:05:14,292 --> 00:05:16,192
I told you she'd love it.

73
00:05:16,260 --> 00:05:18,160
I'm down with the kids.

74
00:05:18,229 --> 00:05:20,720
Oh, yeah, dude. You're the bomb.

75
00:05:20,798 --> 00:05:22,129
Okay.

76
00:05:22,767 --> 00:05:24,894
Listen, you gotta double-pump
the clutch when you shift,

77
00:05:24,969 --> 00:05:27,130
but besides that, you should be good.

78
00:05:27,205 --> 00:05:29,435
That's this one?
- Yeah. Yeah, right there.

79
00:05:29,507 --> 00:05:31,031
All right.

80
00:05:31,843 --> 00:05:33,834
Do you want a ride to school or something?

81
00:05:33,911 --> 00:05:35,936
I go to school on the reservation.

82
00:05:36,247 --> 00:05:38,374
Right, right.
- Yeah.

83
00:05:38,449 --> 00:05:41,611
That's too bad.
It would've been nice to know one person.

84
00:05:42,219 --> 00:05:43,777
(KIDS LAUGHING)

85
00:05:48,091 --> 00:05:50,082
<i>BELLA: My first day at a new school.</i>

86
00:05:50,160 --> 00:05:52,492
<i>It's March, middle of the semester.</i>

87
00:05:52,562 --> 00:05:53,654
(TRUCK BACKFIRES)

88
00:05:53,730 --> 00:05:54,958
<i>Great.</i>

89
00:06:01,772 --> 00:06:04,332
Nice ride.
- Thanks.

90
00:06:05,909 --> 00:06:07,206
Good one.

91
00:06:13,984 --> 00:06:15,975
You're Isabella Swan, the new girl.

92
00:06:16,053 --> 00:06:19,420
Hi, I'm Eric, the eyes and ears of this place.

93
00:06:20,457 --> 00:06:24,324
Anything you need, tour guide,
lunch date, shoulder to cry on?

94
00:06:28,397 --> 00:06:31,833
I'm really kind of the more
suffer-in-silence type.

95
00:06:32,802 --> 00:06:33,826
Good headline for your feature.

96
00:06:33,903 --> 00:06:36,565
I'm on the paper,
and you're news, baby, front page.

97
00:06:36,639 --> 00:06:38,072
No, I'm not.

98
00:06:38,407 --> 00:06:42,241
(STUTTERS) You...
Please don't have any sort of...

99
00:06:42,311 --> 00:06:44,506
Chillax. No feature.

100
00:06:45,047 --> 00:06:46,446
Okay, thanks.
- Cool?

101
00:06:46,582 --> 00:06:48,516
GIRL: All right. Okay. Yeah.

102
00:06:49,351 --> 00:06:50,841
(GIRLS CHATTERING)

103
00:06:52,688 --> 00:06:54,315
GIRL: Get it! Get it! Get it!

104
00:06:54,390 --> 00:06:55,584
(BELLA GRUNTS)

105
00:06:55,658 --> 00:06:57,250
GIRL 1: To you!

106
00:06:57,393 --> 00:06:58,758
Whoa!

107
00:06:58,828 --> 00:06:59,886
I'm sorry.

108
00:06:59,962 --> 00:07:02,226
I told them not to let me play.

109
00:07:02,631 --> 00:07:04,997
No way. No, no, no.
That's... That's... Don't...

110
00:07:05,067 --> 00:07:07,500
You're Isabella, right?

111
00:07:07,569 --> 00:07:09,036
Just Bella.

112
00:07:09,104 --> 00:07:11,265
Yeah. Hey, I'm Mike Newton.

113
00:07:11,573 --> 00:07:13,700
Nice to meet you.
- Yeah, yeah.

114
00:07:13,775 --> 00:07:16,039
She's got a great spike, huh?
- (CHUCKLES) Yeah, it's...

115
00:07:16,111 --> 00:07:17,840
I'm Jessica, by the way.

116
00:07:17,912 --> 00:07:19,846
Hey, you're from Arizona, right?

117
00:07:19,914 --> 00:07:21,245
Yeah.

118
00:07:21,316 --> 00:07:25,047
Aren't people from Arizona
supposed to be, like, really tan?

119
00:07:25,120 --> 00:07:26,178
Yeah.

120
00:07:26,254 --> 00:07:28,848
Maybe that's why they kicked me out.

121
00:07:30,325 --> 00:07:32,293
(MIKE AND JESSICA LAUGHING)

122
00:07:32,360 --> 00:07:33,827
You're good.

123
00:07:35,063 --> 00:07:36,758
That's so funny.

124
00:07:40,568 --> 00:07:42,195
Back in, Jess.
- BOY: Down here.

125
00:07:43,037 --> 00:07:44,299
ERIC: Like a masterpiece, you know,

126
00:07:44,372 --> 00:07:46,636
we'll have, like,
this crazy pyramid fall from the sky,

127
00:07:46,708 --> 00:07:48,642
and then you guys can...
- It's my pleasure, Madame.

128
00:07:48,710 --> 00:07:50,836
You guys can give each other high fives.
- Burrito, my friend?

129
00:07:50,911 --> 00:07:53,539
Hey, Mikey! You met my home girl, Bella?
- Hey.

130
00:07:53,747 --> 00:07:54,941
Your home girl?

131
00:07:55,015 --> 00:07:56,004
Yeah.
- Yeah?

132
00:07:56,083 --> 00:07:57,914
That's...
- My girl.

133
00:07:58,318 --> 00:07:59,785
Sorry I had to mess up your game, Mike!

134
00:07:59,853 --> 00:08:00,842
Tyler.

135
00:08:00,921 --> 00:08:01,945
(ALL LAUGHING)

136
00:08:02,022 --> 00:08:03,250
TYLER: Yes!

137
00:08:03,824 --> 00:08:05,314
Oh, my God.

138
00:08:05,392 --> 00:08:09,453
It's like first grade all over again.
You're the shiny new toy.

139
00:08:09,830 --> 00:08:11,127
Smile.

140
00:08:11,498 --> 00:08:12,760
Okay.
- Sorry.

141
00:08:12,833 --> 00:08:14,232
I needed a candid for the feature.

142
00:08:14,301 --> 00:08:15,700
The feature's dead, Angela.

143
00:08:15,769 --> 00:08:17,828
Don't bring it up again.

144
00:08:18,138 --> 00:08:19,230
It's okay, I just...

145
00:08:19,306 --> 00:08:21,570
I got your back, baby.

146
00:08:21,642 --> 00:08:24,839
Guess we'll just run another editorial
on teen drinking.

147
00:08:24,912 --> 00:08:29,076
You know,
you can always go for eating disorders.

148
00:08:30,617 --> 00:08:32,550
Speedo padding on the swim team.

149
00:08:32,618 --> 00:08:34,176
Actually, that's a good one.

150
00:08:34,253 --> 00:08:37,347
Kirk. Right? That's exactly what I thought.
- (LAUGHS) Yeah.

151
00:08:37,423 --> 00:08:39,584
ANGELA: We're talking Olympic-size.

152
00:08:39,659 --> 00:08:41,752
JESSICA: There's no way. He's so skinny.
It doesn't make sense.

153
00:08:41,828 --> 00:08:43,489
ANGELA: Totally.
- Yeah.

154
00:08:43,930 --> 00:08:45,329
(GIRLS LAUGHING)

155
00:08:46,032 --> 00:08:47,522
Who are they?

156
00:08:48,134 --> 00:08:49,692
The Cullens.

157
00:08:50,803 --> 00:08:54,295
They're Dr. and Mrs. Cullen's foster kids.

158
00:08:54,373 --> 00:08:57,900
They moved down here from Alaska,
like, a few years ago.

159
00:08:57,977 --> 00:09:00,104
They kind of keep to themselves.

160
00:09:00,179 --> 00:09:02,113
Yeah, 'cause they're all together.

161
00:09:02,181 --> 00:09:04,206
Like, together, together.

162
00:09:06,886 --> 00:09:09,446
The blonde girl, that's Rosalie,

163
00:09:09,522 --> 00:09:13,117
and the big dark-haired guy, Emmett,
they're, like, a thing.

164
00:09:13,192 --> 00:09:14,658
I'm not even sure that's legal.

165
00:09:14,726 --> 00:09:17,092
Jess, they're not actually related.

166
00:09:17,162 --> 00:09:19,824
Yeah, but they live together. It's weird.

167
00:09:19,898 --> 00:09:23,527
And, okay, the little dark-haired girl's Alice.

168
00:09:23,602 --> 00:09:25,502
She's really weird,

169
00:09:25,570 --> 00:09:29,734
and she's with Jasper, the blond one
who looks like he's in pain.

170
00:09:33,812 --> 00:09:38,511
Dr. Cullen's like this foster dad/matchmaker.

171
00:09:38,583 --> 00:09:40,574
Maybe he'll adopt me.

172
00:09:41,720 --> 00:09:43,187
Who's he?

173
00:09:49,461 --> 00:09:51,258
That's Edward Cullen.

174
00:09:51,329 --> 00:09:54,127
He's totally gorgeous, obviously,

175
00:09:54,199 --> 00:09:57,531
but apparently nobody here's
good enough for him.

176
00:09:58,469 --> 00:10:00,835
Like I care, you know?

177
00:10:01,405 --> 00:10:02,770
So, yeah.

178
00:10:05,442 --> 00:10:08,275
JESSICA: Seriously, like,
don't waste your time.

179
00:10:08,345 --> 00:10:10,472
I wasn't planning on it.

180
00:10:20,524 --> 00:10:22,492
Mr. Molina.
- Hey, Mike.

181
00:10:23,661 --> 00:10:25,925
Oh, yes. Miss Swan.

182
00:10:40,476 --> 00:10:42,842
Hi. Can I have the pass? Thank you.

183
00:10:42,912 --> 00:10:45,244
Welcome to the class.
Here. Here's your stuff, okay?

184
00:10:45,315 --> 00:10:47,977
And I got a seat for you right here,
so come over.

185
00:10:48,051 --> 00:10:50,383
The last one.
Just follow along till you catch up.

186
00:10:50,453 --> 00:10:54,549
<i>All right, guys, today we are gonna be
observing the behavior of planaria,</i>

187
00:10:54,624 --> 00:10:56,683
aka flatworms.

188
00:10:57,527 --> 00:10:59,688
So what we're gonna do...

189
00:11:00,863 --> 00:11:02,660
(MOLINA CONTINUES
TALKING INDISTINCTLY)

190
00:11:03,900 --> 00:11:05,424
...regenerate.

191
00:11:06,002 --> 00:11:07,492
Zombie worms.

192
00:11:08,404 --> 00:11:12,067
No cell phones. Guys, let's get to it.

193
00:11:13,142 --> 00:11:14,905
Gentle, gentle, certain areas.

194
00:11:14,978 --> 00:11:18,744
Please just don't cut here.
We don't cut here.

195
00:11:18,815 --> 00:11:20,783
You won't believe this.

196
00:11:21,284 --> 00:11:24,878
Let's try to focus
while we check those out, huh, guys?

197
00:11:28,924 --> 00:11:31,154
(SCHOOL BELL RINGING)

198
00:11:35,831 --> 00:11:37,162
EDWARD: There must be something open.

199
00:11:37,232 --> 00:11:40,167
Physics? Biochem?
- WOMAN: No, every class is full.

200
00:11:41,036 --> 00:11:42,594
Just a minute, dear.

201
00:11:42,671 --> 00:11:45,640
I'm afraid you'll have to stay in biology.

202
00:11:46,775 --> 00:11:50,211
Fine. Just... I'll just have to endure it.

203
00:12:06,260 --> 00:12:10,060
I just can't get over how grown up you are.
And so gorgeous.

204
00:12:10,631 --> 00:12:12,656
Hey, Bella.

205
00:12:12,733 --> 00:12:14,394
You remember me?

206
00:12:15,603 --> 00:12:17,730
I played Santa one year.

207
00:12:17,805 --> 00:12:20,968
Yeah, Waylon, she hasn't had
a Christmas here since she was four.

208
00:12:21,042 --> 00:12:23,169
I bet I made an impression, though, didn't I?

209
00:12:23,244 --> 00:12:25,769
You always do.
- Butt-crack Santa?

210
00:12:26,347 --> 00:12:28,338
Hey, kids love those little bottles, though.

211
00:12:28,416 --> 00:12:31,647
All right,
let the girl eat her garden burger, Waylon.

212
00:12:31,719 --> 00:12:34,153
As soon as you're done,
I will bring you your favorite.

213
00:12:34,221 --> 00:12:36,052
Berry cobbler, remember?

214
00:12:36,123 --> 00:12:39,058
Your dad still has it. Every Thursday.

215
00:12:39,126 --> 00:12:41,253
Thank you. That'd be great.

216
00:12:45,933 --> 00:12:47,298
CHARLIE: Here.

217
00:12:47,767 --> 00:12:48,995
(WHISPERS) Thanks.

218
00:12:50,737 --> 00:12:52,398
(PEOPLE LAUGHING)

219
00:12:57,944 --> 00:13:00,708
<i>RENEE ON PHONE: Hey, baby. So, listen,
if spring training goes well,</i>

220
00:13:00,780 --> 00:13:01,940
<i>we could be moving to Florida.</i>

221
00:13:02,015 --> 00:13:05,109
<i>AUTOMATED VOICE: Please insert $1.25
for an additional three minutes.</i>

222
00:13:05,185 --> 00:13:06,379
Mom, where's your cell?

223
00:13:06,453 --> 00:13:07,920
Okay, don't laugh.

224
00:13:07,987 --> 00:13:10,478
I didn't lose my power cord. It ran away.

225
00:13:10,557 --> 00:13:11,546
(LAUGHS)

226
00:13:11,658 --> 00:13:14,889
Screaming. I literally repel technology now.

227
00:13:15,595 --> 00:13:19,053
I miss you.
- Oh, baby, I miss you, too.

228
00:13:19,132 --> 00:13:21,430
But tell me more about your school.
Now, what are the kids like?

229
00:13:21,501 --> 00:13:23,560
<i>Are there any cute guys?</i>

230
00:13:23,636 --> 00:13:25,467
<i>Are they being nice to you?</i>

231
00:13:25,538 --> 00:13:26,630
(SIGHS SOFTLY)

232
00:13:26,706 --> 00:13:27,968
Well,

233
00:13:29,309 --> 00:13:31,469
they're all very welcoming.

234
00:13:32,244 --> 00:13:33,711
Tell me all about it.

235
00:13:33,779 --> 00:13:35,474
It doesn't even matter.

236
00:13:35,547 --> 00:13:36,741
<i>Yes, it does, honey.</i>

237
00:13:36,815 --> 00:13:39,943
I have homework to do. I'll talk to you later.

238
00:13:40,986 --> 00:13:42,385
<i>Okay. I love you.</i>

239
00:13:42,454 --> 00:13:44,046
Love you, too.

240
00:13:53,265 --> 00:13:57,497
<i>BELLA: I planned to confront him
and demand to know what his problem was.</i>

241
00:14:06,512 --> 00:14:08,377
<i>But he never showed.</i>

242
00:14:08,947 --> 00:14:10,539
<i>(SLOW ROCK THEME PLAYING)</i>

243
00:14:14,652 --> 00:14:15,914
Bella!

244
00:14:29,634 --> 00:14:33,070
<i>BELLA: And the next day, another no-show.</i>

245
00:14:38,042 --> 00:14:39,839
<i>More days passed.</i>

246
00:14:40,244 --> 00:14:43,042
<i>Things were getting a little strange.</i>

247
00:14:48,519 --> 00:14:50,077
(PANTING)

