Don't worry, we're gonna find this thing.

760
00:46:33,210 --> 00:46:34,643
Meantime,

761
00:46:35,913 --> 00:46:38,347
I want you to carry this with you.

762
00:46:40,785 --> 00:46:44,949
I don't know if you...
- It'll give your old man some peace of mind.

763
00:46:45,022 --> 00:46:46,284
Okay.

764
00:46:49,560 --> 00:46:51,221
Let's go home.

765
00:47:36,839 --> 00:47:38,204
Cold One.

766
00:48:17,212 --> 00:48:18,872
<i>(ECHOING BOOM)</i>

767
00:49:40,126 --> 00:49:42,117
(BREATH TREMBLING)

768
00:49:45,431 --> 00:49:48,229
You're impossibly fast and strong.

769
00:49:49,568 --> 00:49:52,469
Your skin is pale white and ice-cold.

770
00:49:53,439 --> 00:49:55,373
Your eyes change color.

771
00:49:56,308 --> 00:50:00,608
And sometimes you speak
like you're from a different time.

772
00:50:02,248 --> 00:50:06,378
You never eat or drink anything.
You don't go out in the sunlight.

773
00:50:07,820 --> 00:50:09,481
(BELLA GASPS QUIETLY)

774
00:50:09,555 --> 00:50:11,250
How old are you?

775
00:50:12,625 --> 00:50:14,115
Seventeen.

776
00:50:16,362 --> 00:50:18,489
How long have you been 17?

777
00:50:21,967 --> 00:50:23,366
A while.

778
00:50:36,414 --> 00:50:38,279
I know what you are.

779
00:50:40,752 --> 00:50:42,185
Say it.

780
00:50:45,690 --> 00:50:47,089
Out loud.

781
00:50:49,994 --> 00:50:51,325
Say it.

782
00:50:57,268 --> 00:50:58,565
Vampire.

783
00:51:02,006 --> 00:51:03,598
Are you afraid?

784
00:51:05,009 --> 00:51:06,237
(BREATH TREMBLING)

785
00:51:11,815 --> 00:51:12,873
No.

786
00:51:15,485 --> 00:51:18,454
Then ask me the most basic question.

787
00:51:18,522 --> 00:51:20,217
What do we eat?

788
00:51:23,160 --> 00:51:24,957
You won't hurt me.

789
00:51:29,900 --> 00:51:31,731
Where are we going?

790
00:51:32,936 --> 00:51:34,096
Up the mountain.

791
00:51:34,171 --> 00:51:36,139
Out of the cloud bank.

792
00:51:36,206 --> 00:51:39,369
You need to see what
I look like in the sunlight.

793
00:51:54,023 --> 00:51:55,422
(BELLA PANTING)

794
00:51:58,494 --> 00:52:01,054
This is why we don't show
ourselves in sunlight.

795
00:52:01,130 --> 00:52:03,598
People would know we're different.

796
00:52:13,776 --> 00:52:15,539
This is what I am.

797
00:52:18,147 --> 00:52:20,342
(GASPING)

798
00:52:20,983 --> 00:52:22,917
It's like diamonds.

799
00:52:31,494 --> 00:52:33,189
You're beautiful.

800
00:52:36,364 --> 00:52:37,922
Beautiful?

801
00:52:37,999 --> 00:52:40,627
This is the skin of a killer, Bella.

802
00:52:47,142 --> 00:52:48,666
I'm a killer.

803
00:52:50,779 --> 00:52:52,679
I don't believe that.

804
00:52:53,348 --> 00:52:55,942
That's because you believe the lie.

805
00:52:56,551 --> 00:52:58,178
It's camouflage.

806
00:53:00,488 --> 00:53:03,355
I'm the world's most dangerous predator.

807
00:53:04,159 --> 00:53:07,322
Everything about me invites you in,

808
00:53:07,896 --> 00:53:11,229
my voice, my face, even my smell.

809
00:53:12,300 --> 00:53:14,825
As if I would need any of that.

810
00:53:14,969 --> 00:53:17,062
(LOUD WHOOSH)

811
00:53:17,538 --> 00:53:19,699
As if you could outrun me!

812
00:53:21,742 --> 00:53:23,300
(WHOOSHING)

813
00:53:25,446 --> 00:53:27,710
As if you could fight me off.

814
00:53:31,151 --> 00:53:33,051
I'm designed to kill.

815
00:53:35,989 --> 00:53:37,650
I don't care.

816
00:53:38,492 --> 00:53:40,619
I've killed people before.

817
00:53:42,396 --> 00:53:44,193
It does not matter.

818
00:53:48,869 --> 00:53:50,734
I wanted to kill you.

819
00:53:54,208 --> 00:53:58,645
I've never wanted a human's blood
so much in my life.

820
00:53:59,912 --> 00:54:01,436
I trust you.

821
00:54:03,950 --> 00:54:05,247
Don't.

822
00:54:06,586 --> 00:54:08,520
I'm here. I trust you.

823
00:54:08,588 --> 00:54:09,748
(WHOOSH)

824
00:54:13,092 --> 00:54:16,323
My family,
we're different from others of our kind.

825
00:54:16,395 --> 00:54:18,158
We only hunt animals.

826
00:54:18,231 --> 00:54:20,859
We've learned to control our thirst.

827
00:54:21,567 --> 00:54:24,297
But it's you, your scent,

828
00:54:26,806 --> 00:54:29,036
it's like a drug to me.

829
00:54:30,443 --> 00:54:34,277
You're like
my own personal brand of heroin.

830
00:54:37,016 --> 00:54:38,005
(WHOOSH)

831
00:54:41,320 --> 00:54:44,482
Why did you hate me
so much when we met?

832
00:54:44,556 --> 00:54:46,023
I did.

833
00:54:46,324 --> 00:54:49,054
Only for making me want you so badly.

834
00:54:49,661 --> 00:54:52,630
I still don't know if I can control myself.

835
00:54:54,599 --> 00:54:56,260
I know you can.

836
00:55:04,676 --> 00:55:06,735
I can't read your mind.

837
00:55:07,412 --> 00:55:10,381
You have to tell me what you're thinking.

838
00:55:12,851 --> 00:55:14,546
Now I'm afraid.

839
00:55:19,558 --> 00:55:20,889
Good.

840
00:55:22,027 --> 00:55:23,961
I'm not afraid of you.

841
00:55:27,698 --> 00:55:31,794
I'm only afraid of losing you.
I feel like you're gonna disappear.

842
00:55:38,909 --> 00:55:41,901
You don't know how long
I've waited for you.

843
00:55:50,120 --> 00:55:52,953
So the lion fell in love with the lamb.

844
00:55:56,560 --> 00:55:58,391
What a stupid lamb.

845
00:55:58,462 --> 00:56:01,056
What a sick, masochistic lion.

846
00:56:03,567 --> 00:56:05,330
<i>(GENTLE THEME PLAYING)</i>

847
00:57:26,648 --> 00:57:29,742
<i>BELLA: About three things
I was absolutely positive.</i>

848
00:57:31,119 --> 00:57:32,279
<i>First,</i>

849
00:57:33,587 --> 00:57:35,418
<i>Edward was a vampire.</i>

850
00:57:39,994 --> 00:57:41,256
<i>Second,</i>

851
00:57:42,063 --> 00:57:43,997
<i>there was a part of him,</i>

852
00:57:44,065 --> 00:57:46,192
<i>and I didn't know
how dominant that part might be,</i>

853
00:57:46,267 --> 00:57:47,632
(HORN HONKS TWICE)

854
00:57:47,702 --> 00:57:49,897
<i>that thirsted for my blood.</i>

855
00:57:53,841 --> 00:57:55,331
<i>And third,</i>

856
00:57:56,410 --> 00:58:00,210
<i>I was unconditionally and irrevocably
in love with him.</i>

857
00:58:05,853 --> 00:58:08,947
JESSICA: Monte Carlo?
That's our prom theme?

858
00:58:09,023 --> 00:58:13,722
Gambling, tuxedos, and Bond, James Bond.

859
00:58:14,995 --> 00:58:16,689
(ENGINE PURRS)

860
00:58:17,664 --> 00:58:19,632
Oh, my God.

861
00:58:19,799 --> 00:58:21,630
<i>(UP-TEMPO ROCK THEME PLAYING)</i>

862
00:58:28,541 --> 00:58:29,701
Wow.

863
00:58:29,776 --> 00:58:30,936
(CLEARS THROAT)

864
00:58:31,878 --> 00:58:34,210
You know, everybody's staring.

865
00:58:38,151 --> 00:58:41,518
Not that guy. No, he just looked.

866
00:58:43,957 --> 00:58:46,755
I'm breaking all the rules now anyway.

867
00:58:46,826 --> 00:58:48,953
Since I'm going to hell.

868
00:58:53,366 --> 00:58:56,164
So, does a person have to be dying

869
00:58:58,737 --> 00:59:00,637
to become like you?

870
00:59:01,206 --> 00:59:04,175
No, that's just Carlisle.

871
00:59:05,744 --> 00:59:09,202
He'd never do this to someone
who had another choice.

872
00:59:10,783 --> 00:59:13,479
So, how long have you been like this?

873
00:59:14,419 --> 00:59:15,977
Since 1918.

874
00:59:16,822 --> 00:59:20,553
<i>That's when Carlisle found me
dying of Spanish influenza.</i>

875
00:59:22,694 --> 00:59:23,854
<i>BELLA: What was it like?</i>

876
00:59:23,929 --> 00:59:24,953
(YELLS)

877
00:59:25,030 --> 00:59:27,396
<i>EDWARD: The venom was excruciating.</i>

878
00:59:28,100 --> 00:59:30,261
<i>But what Carlisle did was much harder.</i>

879
00:59:30,335 --> 00:59:32,803
<i>Not many of us have the restraint to do that.</i>

880
00:59:32,871 --> 00:59:35,533
But didn't he just have to bite?

881
00:59:37,776 --> 00:59:39,243
Not exactly.

882
00:59:39,812 --> 00:59:41,574
When we taste

883
00:59:43,714 --> 00:59:47,150
human blood, a sort of frenzy begins,

884
00:59:48,653 --> 00:59:51,144
and it's almost impossible to stop.

885
00:59:53,357 --> 00:59:55,086
<i>BELLA: But Carlisle did.</i>

886
00:59:55,159 --> 00:59:57,992
<i>EDWARD: First with me
and then with his wife, Esme.</i>

887
00:59:58,062 --> 01:00:02,590
So is Carlisle the real reason
that you don't kill people?

888
01:00:06,270 --> 01:00:08,534
No, he's not the only reason.

889
01:00:11,075 --> 01:00:13,771
I don't want to be a monster.

890
01:00:15,413 --> 01:00:19,543
My family,
we think of ourselves as vegetarians, right,

891
01:00:19,617 --> 01:00:22,950
'cause we only survive
on the blood of animals.

892
01:00:23,020 --> 01:00:24,486
But it's...

893
01:00:25,322 --> 01:00:28,018
It's like a human only living on tofu.

894
01:00:28,091 --> 01:00:32,619
It keeps you strong,
but you're never fully satisfied.

895
01:00:35,732 --> 01:00:39,168
It wouldn't be like drinking your blood,
for instance.

896
01:00:44,574 --> 01:00:47,634
Was it other vampires that killed Waylon?

897
01:00:47,711 --> 01:00:48,973
Yeah.

898
01:00:49,045 --> 01:00:53,311
There are others out there,
and we run into them from time to time.

899
01:00:55,285 --> 01:00:59,221
Can the rest of your family
read people's minds like you can?

900
01:01:02,292 --> 01:01:04,157
No. That's just me.

901
01:01:04,928 --> 01:01:07,760
But Alice can see the future.

902
01:01:08,797 --> 01:01:10,788
I bet she saw me coming.

903
01:01:12,134 --> 01:01:14,568
Alice's visions are subjective.

904
01:01:15,004 --> 01:01:17,802
I mean, the future can always change.

905
01:01:24,780 --> 01:01:25,769
(LOUD BANG)

906
01:01:28,250 --> 01:01:30,980
Could you act human?
I mean, I've got neighbors.

907
01:01:31,053 --> 01:01:33,920
I'm gonna take you to my place tomorrow.

908
01:01:35,391 --> 01:01:36,790
Thanks.

909
01:01:37,259 --> 01:01:40,194
Wait, like, with your family?
- Yeah.

910
01:01:41,497 --> 01:01:43,658
What if they don't like me?

911
01:01:44,533 --> 01:01:48,128
So, you're worried not because
you'll be in a house full of vampires,

912
01:01:48,203 --> 01:01:51,330
but because you think
they won't approve of you?

913
01:01:51,639 --> 01:01:53,539
I'm glad I amuse you.

914
01:01:55,109 --> 01:01:56,667
What is it?

915
01:01:57,979 --> 01:01:59,571
Complication.

916
01:02:01,616 --> 01:02:03,709
I'll pick you up tomorrow.

917
01:02:29,444 --> 01:02:32,378
Hey. Come to visit your truck?

918
01:02:33,547 --> 01:02:35,981
Looks good. Got that dent out.

919
01:02:36,049 --> 01:02:38,677
Yeah.
- Actually, we came to visit your flat-screen.

920
01:02:38,752 --> 01:02:40,982
First Mariners game of the season.

921
01:02:41,054 --> 01:02:44,785
Plus Jacob here keeps bugging me about
seeing you again.

922
01:02:44,858 --> 01:02:46,792
Great, Dad. Thanks.

923
01:02:46,860 --> 01:02:49,055
Just keeping it real, son.

924
01:02:50,430 --> 01:02:52,193
CHARLIE: Vitamin R.

925
01:02:52,265 --> 01:02:53,994
Well done, Chief.

926
01:02:54,067 --> 01:02:56,467
Harry Clearwater's homemade fish fry.

927
01:02:56,536 --> 01:02:58,026
Good man.

928
01:03:00,407 --> 01:03:02,204
Any luck with that Waylon case?

929
01:03:02,275 --> 01:03:05,073
Well, I don't think it was an animal
that killed him.

930
01:03:05,145 --> 01:03:07,204
Never thought it was.

931
01:03:08,715 --> 01:03:10,444
So spread the word out at the rez, huh?

932
01:03:10,517 --> 01:03:12,075
Keep the kids out of the woods.

933
01:03:12,152 --> 01:03:13,449
Will do.

934
01:03:14,253 --> 01:03:17,222
Don't want no one else getting hurt, do we?

935
01:03:20,192 --> 01:03:22,057
<i>(SLOW, EXOTIC THEME PLAYING)</i>

936
01:03:47,787 --> 01:03:48,811
(EXHALES)

937
01:03:48,888 --> 01:03:50,116
Whoa.

938
01:03:51,223 --> 01:03:52,986
This is incredible.

939
01:03:56,095 --> 01:03:58,756
It's so light and open, you know?

940
01:04:00,398 --> 01:04:04,391
What did you expect,
coffins and dungeons and moats?

941
01:04:04,903 --> 01:04:07,303
(CHUCKLES) No, not the moats.

942
01:04:08,306 --> 01:04:09,933
Not the moats.

943
01:04:16,648 --> 01:04:19,617
This is the one place we don't have to hide.

944
01:04:20,685 --> 01:04:22,084
<i>(OPERATIC MUSIC PLAYING IN DISTANCE)</i>

945
01:04:22,153 --> 01:04:23,984
I told them not to do this.

946
01:04:24,055 --> 01:04:27,718
<i>MAN ON TV: You add a little bit of olive oil
to a non-stick saut pan,</i>

947
01:04:27,792 --> 01:04:31,193
<i>and you want to cook
with the olive oil in medium-high heat.</i>

948
01:04:31,262 --> 01:04:35,028
<i>What I do, I cut this in strips,
and then we gonna cut this...</i>

949
01:04:35,100 --> 01:04:38,228
Is she even Italian?
- Her name is Bella.

950
01:04:38,303 --> 01:04:41,271
I'm sure she'll love it, no matter what.

951
01:04:41,338 --> 01:04:43,135
ROSALIE: (SIGHS) Get a whiff of that.

952
01:04:43,707 --> 01:04:45,834
(SINGSONG) Here comes the human.

953
01:04:49,713 --> 01:04:52,341
Bella, we're making Italiano for you.

954
01:04:53,517 --> 01:04:57,954
Bella, this is Esme.
My mother for all intents and purposes.

955
01:04:58,021 --> 01:05:00,581
<i>(SPEAKING ITALIAN)</i>

956
01:05:00,657 --> 01:05:02,955
You've given us an excuse
to use the kitchen for the first time.

957
01:05:03,026 --> 01:05:04,186
I hope you're hungry.

958
01:05:04,261 --> 01:05:06,889
Yeah, absolutely.
- She already ate.

959
01:05:13,303 --> 01:05:14,634
Perfect.

960
01:05:15,205 --> 01:05:19,198
Yeah, it's just because
I know that you guys don't eat...

961
01:05:19,276 --> 01:05:21,767
Of course. It's very considerate of you.

962
01:05:21,845 --> 01:05:24,404
Just ignore Rosalie. I do.
- ROSALIE: Yeah.

963
01:05:24,480 --> 01:05:27,643
Let's just keep pretending
like this isn't dangerous for all of us.

964
01:05:27,717 --> 01:05:31,278
I would never tell anybody anything.

965
01:05:31,954 --> 01:05:33,717
She knows that.

966
01:05:33,789 --> 01:05:36,883
Yeah, well, the problem is,
you two have gone public now, so...

967
01:05:36,959 --> 01:05:37,948
Emmett.

968
01:05:38,027 --> 01:05:39,722
No, she should know.

969
01:05:39,795 --> 01:05:43,492
The entire family
will be implicated if this ends badly.

970
01:05:44,000 --> 01:05:45,695
Badly, as in...

971
01:05:47,303 --> 01:05:49,669
I would become the meal.

972
01:05:50,273 --> 01:05:51,706
(SNICKERING)

973
01:05:52,942 --> 01:05:54,671
(LAUGHING)

974
01:05:57,046 --> 01:05:58,445
Hi, Bella.

975
01:06:02,251 --> 01:06:03,741
I'm Alice.

976
01:06:04,686 --> 01:06:05,983
Hi.
- Hi.

977
01:06:07,856 --> 01:06:09,756
You do smell good.

978
01:06:09,824 --> 01:06:10,984
Alice, what are you...

979
01:06:11,059 --> 01:06:14,517
It's okay.
Bella and I are gonna be great friends.

980
01:06:17,866 --> 01:06:20,334
CARLISLE: Sorry,
Jasper's our newest vegetarian.

981
01:06:20,402 --> 01:06:22,495
It's a little difficult for him.

982
01:06:22,571 --> 01:06:24,471
It's a pleasure to meet you.

983
01:06:24,539 --> 01:06:27,337
It's okay, Jasper. You won't hurt her.

984
01:06:28,810 --> 01:06:32,439
All right, I'm gonna take you
on a tour of the rest of the house.

985
01:06:32,514 --> 01:06:34,812
Okay.
- Well, I'll see you soon.

986
01:06:34,883 --> 01:06:36,111
Okay.

987
01:06:38,086 --> 01:06:39,644
Cute!
- I know.

988
01:06:40,222 --> 01:06:41,450
I think that went well.

989
01:06:41,523 --> 01:06:43,923
Clean this up. Now.

990
01:06:43,992 --> 01:06:47,119
Was that as weird for you as it was for me?

991
01:06:47,194 --> 01:06:48,991
I don't know.

992
01:06:54,668 --> 01:06:56,329
Graduation caps?

993
01:06:57,504 --> 01:07:00,337
Yeah. It's a private joke.

994
01:07:01,242 --> 01:07:03,176
We matriculate a lot.

995
01:07:04,712 --> 01:07:06,612
That's kind of miserable.

996
01:07:06,680 --> 01:07:09,547
I mean, repeating high school
over and over.

997
01:07:09,617 --> 01:07:11,710
True, but the younger we start out
in a new place,

998
01:07:11,785 --> 01:07:13,912
the longer we can stay there.

999
01:07:13,988 --> 01:07:15,512
Come on.

1000
01:07:25,766 --> 01:07:27,666
Yeah, this is my room.

1001
01:07:36,943 --> 01:07:38,410
(BIRDS CHIRPING OUTSIDE)

1002
01:07:40,513 --> 01:07:41,878
No bed?

1003
01:07:42,448 --> 01:07:44,006
No, I don't...

1004
01:07:44,784 --> 01:07:46,342
I don't sleep.

1005
01:07:47,186 --> 01:07:49,518
Ever?
- No, not at all.

1006
01:07:51,190 --> 01:07:52,657
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

1007
01:07:52,725 --> 01:07:54,022
Okay.

1008
01:08:02,435 --> 01:08:04,733
Boy, you have so much music.

1009
01:08:05,505 --> 01:08:07,700
What are you listening to?

1010
01:08:07,774 --> 01:08:08,536
(BUTTON CLICKS)

1011
01:08:09,842 --> 01:08:11,104
<i>(CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING)</i>

1012
01:08:11,177 --> 01:08:12,700
It's Debussy.

1013
01:08:15,180 --> 01:08:17,080
I don't know...
- Yeah.

1014
01:08:20,886 --> 01:08:23,184
<i>Claire De Lune is great.</i>

1015
01:08:57,822 --> 01:09:00,518
What?
- I can't dance.

1016
01:09:01,325 --> 01:09:02,792
