01:27:47,224 --> 01:27:48,213
(DOOR SLAMS)

1271
01:28:11,013 --> 01:28:13,379
Your father's gonna forgive you.

1272
01:28:14,750 --> 01:28:17,082
Why don't you let me drive?

1273
01:28:22,758 --> 01:28:24,191
He won't.

1274
01:28:25,294 --> 01:28:27,455
You should've seen his face.

1275
01:28:29,265 --> 01:28:31,028
I told him the same thing
that my mom told him

1276
01:28:31,100 --> 01:28:32,727
when she was leaving him.

1277
01:28:32,802 --> 01:28:35,396
It's the only way he'd let you go.

1278
01:28:38,140 --> 01:28:42,509
Just don't worry about him now.
He's safe. The tracker's following us.

1279
01:28:42,578 --> 01:28:43,772
(LOUD BANG)

1280
01:28:43,846 --> 01:28:45,211
(GASPS)

1281
01:28:45,281 --> 01:28:47,476
Oh, God.
- It's just Emmett.

1282
01:28:49,618 --> 01:28:51,950
Alice is in the car behind us.

1283
01:28:55,223 --> 01:28:57,316
<i>(MELANCHOLY THEME PLAYING)</i>

1284
01:29:13,608 --> 01:29:14,836
CARLISLE: Wait.

1285
01:29:15,844 --> 01:29:18,312
He came to warn us about James.

1286
01:29:18,680 --> 01:29:22,673
This isn't my fight,
and I've grown tired of his games,

1287
01:29:22,751 --> 01:29:25,686
but he's got unparalleled senses,
absolutely lethal.

1288
01:29:25,754 --> 01:29:28,746
I've never seen anything like him
in my 300 years.

1289
01:29:28,823 --> 01:29:32,690
And the woman, Victoria,
don't underestimate her.

1290
01:29:37,665 --> 01:29:38,859
I've had to fight our kind before.

1291
01:29:38,933 --> 01:29:41,959
They're not easy to kill.
- EMMETT: But not impossible.

1292
01:29:42,369 --> 01:29:44,462
We'll tear them apart and burn the pieces.

1293
01:29:44,538 --> 01:29:46,438
I don't relish the thought
of killing another creature,

1294
01:29:46,507 --> 01:29:49,032
even a sadistic one like James.

1295
01:29:49,109 --> 01:29:52,408
What if he kills one of us first?
- I'm gonna run Bella south.

1296
01:29:52,479 --> 01:29:53,639
Can you lead the tracker away from here?

1297
01:29:53,714 --> 01:29:55,648
No, Edward.
James knows you would never leave Bella.

1298
01:29:55,716 --> 01:29:57,741
He'll follow you.
- ALICE: I'll go with Bella.

1299
01:29:57,818 --> 01:29:59,911
Jasper and I will drive her south.

1300
01:29:59,987 --> 01:30:01,318
I'll keep her safe, Edward.

1301
01:30:01,388 --> 01:30:04,516
Can you keep your thoughts to yourself?
- Yes.

1302
01:30:08,295 --> 01:30:10,229
Rosalie, Esme,

1303
01:30:11,265 --> 01:30:15,325
could you put these on
so the tracker will pick up Bella's scent?

1304
01:30:17,604 --> 01:30:19,970
Why? What is she to me?

1305
01:30:20,039 --> 01:30:22,906
Rosalie, Bella is with Edward.

1306
01:30:22,976 --> 01:30:25,342
She's part of this family now,

1307
01:30:26,713 --> 01:30:29,011
and we protect our family.

1308
01:30:46,366 --> 01:30:48,493
Oh, God. If anything...

1309
01:30:48,568 --> 01:30:49,796
What if...

1310
01:30:49,869 --> 01:30:51,666
If anything happens, I swear to God...

1311
01:30:51,738 --> 01:30:53,706
Nothing's gonna happen.

1312
01:30:53,773 --> 01:30:56,468
There's seven of us,
and there's two of them,

1313
01:30:56,541 --> 01:31:00,204
and when everything's done,
I'm gonna come back and get you.

1314
01:31:00,278 --> 01:31:01,438
Yeah.

1315
01:31:02,180 --> 01:31:04,307
Bella, you are my life now.

1316
01:31:06,985 --> 01:31:08,782
(ENGINES STARTING)

1317
01:31:21,967 --> 01:31:23,764
Hey, Mom. It's me again.

1318
01:31:23,835 --> 01:31:25,769
You must have let your phone die
or something.

1319
01:31:25,837 --> 01:31:30,001
I'm not in Forks, but everything's okay,
and I'll explain it later.

1320
01:31:37,315 --> 01:31:39,305
EDWARD: Rosalie, mark the tree.

1321
01:31:41,485 --> 01:31:43,282
That's good.

1322
01:32:04,175 --> 01:32:05,608
(GROWLS)

1323
01:32:10,548 --> 01:32:12,038
(INHALES DEEPLY)

1324
01:32:28,765 --> 01:32:29,959
(GASPS)

1325
01:32:30,033 --> 01:32:32,194
What is it? What do you see?

1326
01:32:34,571 --> 01:32:36,163
(LOW RUMBLING)

1327
01:32:37,440 --> 01:32:39,169
(FIERCE GROWLING)

1328
01:32:44,280 --> 01:32:45,838
He's figured it out.

1329
01:32:45,915 --> 01:32:48,713
The tracker, he just changed course.

1330
01:32:50,520 --> 01:32:52,181
Where will it take him, Alice?
- Mirrors.

1331
01:32:52,255 --> 01:32:54,246
A room full of mirrors.

1332
01:32:58,528 --> 01:33:01,622
Edward said the visions
weren't always certain.

1333
01:33:01,698 --> 01:33:03,996
JASPER: She sees the course people
are on while they're on it.

1334
01:33:04,067 --> 01:33:06,159
If they change their minds,
the vision changes.

1335
01:33:06,235 --> 01:33:08,465
Okay, so the course that
the tracker's on now

1336
01:33:08,537 --> 01:33:11,131
is gonna lead him to a ballet studio?

1337
01:33:11,940 --> 01:33:14,932
You've been here?
- I took lessons as a kid.

1338
01:33:15,744 --> 01:33:17,609
The school I went to
had an arch just like that.

1339
01:33:17,679 --> 01:33:18,907
Was your school here in Phoenix?

1340
01:33:18,981 --> 01:33:20,243
Yeah.

1341
01:33:20,315 --> 01:33:21,304
(PHONE VIBRATES)

1342
01:33:21,984 --> 01:33:23,884
Edward, are you okay?
- We've lost the tracker.

1343
01:33:23,952 --> 01:33:25,510
The woman's still in the area.

1344
01:33:25,587 --> 01:33:28,181
Rosalie and Esme are going back
to Forks to protect your father.

1345
01:33:28,257 --> 01:33:34,218
I'm coming to get you. Then you and I
are gonna go somewhere alone.

1346
01:33:34,296 --> 01:33:35,957
<i>And the others will keep hunting.</i>

1347
01:33:36,031 --> 01:33:39,228
I'll do whatever it takes
to make you safe again.

1348
01:33:45,841 --> 01:33:47,432
(PHONE VIBRATING)

1349
01:33:51,045 --> 01:33:53,309
Hey, Mom, I'm glad you got my message.

1350
01:33:53,381 --> 01:33:54,575
What are you doing home?

1351
01:33:54,649 --> 01:33:57,277
<i>Bella? Bella? Bella, where are you?</i>

1352
01:33:58,252 --> 01:34:01,221
<i>Calm down, everything's fine.
- Bella? Bella?</i>

1353
01:34:01,289 --> 01:34:03,723
I'll explain everything later.

1354
01:34:03,825 --> 01:34:04,849
Mom, are you there?

1355
01:34:04,926 --> 01:34:08,987
<i>JAMES: Forks High School doesn't protect
its students' privacy very well.</i>

1356
01:34:09,063 --> 01:34:13,363
It was just too easy for Victoria
to find your previous address.

1357
01:34:13,434 --> 01:34:15,868
<i>It's a nice house you have here.</i>

1358
01:34:15,937 --> 01:34:18,201
<i>I was prepared to wait for you,</i>

1359
01:34:18,272 --> 01:34:22,902
<i>but then Mom came home after she received
a very worried call from your dad,</i>

1360
01:34:23,611 --> 01:34:26,045
<i>and it all worked out quite well.</i>

1361
01:34:26,747 --> 01:34:27,873
<i>RENEE: Wait, wait...</i>

1362
01:34:27,949 --> 01:34:29,246
Don't touch her! Don't...

1363
01:34:29,317 --> 01:34:31,648
<i>You can still save her.
- BELLA: Don't!</i>

1364
01:34:31,718 --> 01:34:33,913
<i>But you're gonna have to get away
from your friends.</i>

1365
01:34:33,987 --> 01:34:37,115
<i>Can you handle that?
- Where should I meet you?</i>

1366
01:34:39,125 --> 01:34:41,616
How about your old ballet studio?

1367
01:34:42,262 --> 01:34:45,163
<i>And I'll know if you bring anyone along.</i>

1368
01:34:47,100 --> 01:34:50,399
<i>Poor Mommy would
pay the price for that mistake.</i>

1369
01:35:07,320 --> 01:35:10,619
<i>BELLA: I'd never given much thought
to how I would die.</i>

1370
01:35:11,191 --> 01:35:15,593
<i>But dying in the place of someone I love
seems like a good way to go.</i>

1371
01:35:23,602 --> 01:35:28,266
<i>I can't bring myself to regret the decisions
that brought me face-to-face with death.</i>

1372
01:35:28,340 --> 01:35:30,706
<i>They also brought me to Edward.</i>

1373
01:35:59,604 --> 01:36:02,835
RENEE: Bella? Bella? Bella, where are you?

1374
01:36:02,907 --> 01:36:04,169
Mom?
- Bella?

1375
01:36:04,242 --> 01:36:05,766
Mom?
- There you are.

1376
01:36:05,843 --> 01:36:07,310
<i>RENEE: What are you doing in here?</i>

1377
01:36:07,378 --> 01:36:09,437
<i>YOUNG BELLA: Everyone makes fun of me.</i>

1378
01:36:10,114 --> 01:36:12,708
<i>Come on, you're a wonderful dancer.</i>

1379
01:36:12,784 --> 01:36:14,843
<i>Mom, I suck.</i>

1380
01:36:15,019 --> 01:36:16,179
(JAMES LAUGHING)

1381
01:36:16,254 --> 01:36:17,949
<i>You do not suck.</i>

1382
01:36:27,966 --> 01:36:30,059
That's my favorite part.

1383
01:36:30,969 --> 01:36:33,767
You were a stubborn child, weren't you?

1384
01:36:35,707 --> 01:36:37,867
She's not even here.
- No.

1385
01:36:40,143 --> 01:36:41,508
JAMES: Sorry.

1386
01:36:41,945 --> 01:36:45,005
You know, but you really made it too easy.

1387
01:36:45,082 --> 01:36:48,381
So to make things more entertaining,

1388
01:36:48,986 --> 01:36:52,217
I'm gonna make a little film
of our time together.

1389
01:36:53,824 --> 01:36:57,225
I borrowed this from your house.
I hope you don't mind.

1390
01:36:57,294 --> 01:36:58,454
Good.

1391
01:36:58,528 --> 01:36:59,859
And

1392
01:37:01,031 --> 01:37:02,362
action.

1393
01:37:04,768 --> 01:37:06,497
That'll break Edward's little heart.

1394
01:37:06,570 --> 01:37:08,936
You have...
Edward has nothing to do with this!

1395
01:37:09,006 --> 01:37:10,667
But he does.

1396
01:37:11,708 --> 01:37:14,370
His rage will make for more interesting sport

1397
01:37:14,444 --> 01:37:17,902
than his feeble attempt to protect you.

1398
01:37:19,216 --> 01:37:21,046
And let's continue.

1399
01:37:26,055 --> 01:37:27,454
(GROWLS)

1400
01:37:27,690 --> 01:37:29,248
(WHOOSHING)

1401
01:37:31,827 --> 01:37:33,351
(BELLA YELLS)

1402
01:37:33,429 --> 01:37:35,021
(GRUNTING)

1403
01:37:35,097 --> 01:37:36,086
(GROANS)

1404
01:37:36,198 --> 01:37:39,497
Beautiful. Very visually dynamic.

1405
01:37:42,505 --> 01:37:44,564
I chose my stage well.

1406
01:37:49,745 --> 01:37:53,237
It's too bad he didn't have
the strength to turn you.

1407
01:37:53,582 --> 01:37:56,312
Instead, he kept you
this fragile little human.

1408
01:37:56,385 --> 01:37:58,319
It's cruel, really.

1409
01:38:01,824 --> 01:38:02,949
(SCREAMS)

1410
01:38:03,024 --> 01:38:05,356
Tell Edward how much it hurts.

1411
01:38:05,427 --> 01:38:07,019
Tell him to avenge you. Tell him!

1412
01:38:07,095 --> 01:38:09,893
No, Edward, don't!
- Tell him! Tell him!

1413
01:38:09,964 --> 01:38:11,591
(YELLING)

1414
01:38:16,104 --> 01:38:17,799
(PANTS)

1415
01:38:19,908 --> 01:38:21,535
(JAMES GROWLING)

1416
01:38:22,644 --> 01:38:26,102
You're alone
'cause you're faster than the others.

1417
01:38:28,416 --> 01:38:30,077
But not stronger.

1418
01:38:31,619 --> 01:38:34,087
I'm strong enough to kill you.

1419
01:38:35,290 --> 01:38:36,882
(YELLS)

1420
01:38:40,862 --> 01:38:42,420
I'm sorry.

1421
01:38:43,832 --> 01:38:45,298
(JAMES GRUNTS)

1422
01:38:45,365 --> 01:38:46,662
(BELLA SCREAMING)

1423
01:38:52,940 --> 01:38:54,532
(GROANS)

1424
01:39:03,584 --> 01:39:05,347
(BELLA SCREAMING)

1425
01:39:09,423 --> 01:39:10,947
(BELLA GASPING)

1426
01:39:11,658 --> 01:39:13,091
(GRUNTING)

1427
01:39:15,829 --> 01:39:17,387
(GROWLING)

1428
01:39:29,408 --> 01:39:31,239
(BOTH GROWLING)

1429
01:39:35,314 --> 01:39:37,009
(YELLING)

1430
01:39:38,251 --> 01:39:39,684
(RAPID GASPING)

1431
01:39:46,359 --> 01:39:47,417
Bella, Bella, it's okay.

1432
01:39:47,493 --> 01:39:49,927
Son. Enough.

1433
01:39:50,730 --> 01:39:52,664
Remember who you are.

1434
01:39:55,501 --> 01:39:56,832
(BELLA YELLING)

1435
01:39:57,537 --> 01:39:58,765
ALICE: Bella, you're okay.

1436
01:39:58,838 --> 01:40:00,499
Bella needs you.

1437
01:40:00,907 --> 01:40:02,602
It's okay.

1438
01:40:02,675 --> 01:40:04,040
Oh, God.

1439
01:40:07,813 --> 01:40:09,713
Carlisle? Her blood.

1440
01:40:09,782 --> 01:40:11,373
Your brothers will take care of him.
- I got him.

1441
01:40:11,449 --> 01:40:12,711
ALICE: Carlisle!
- Start the fire.

1442
01:40:12,784 --> 01:40:15,514
EMMETT: Get the floorboards.

1443
01:40:15,720 --> 01:40:17,813
JASPER: Alice!
- Alice, go.

1444
01:40:27,799 --> 01:40:29,824
Her femoral artery's been severed.
She's losing too much blood.

1445
01:40:29,901 --> 01:40:32,131
No, no, my head is burning!

1446
01:40:33,638 --> 01:40:35,367
It's the venom.

1447
01:40:36,241 --> 01:40:40,007
You have to make a choice.
You could let the change happen.

1448
01:40:40,078 --> 01:40:41,375
No.

1449
01:40:42,080 --> 01:40:43,274
No.

1450
01:40:44,616 --> 01:40:48,347
It's gonna happen, Edward. I've seen it.
- It doesn't have to be that way.

1451
01:40:48,420 --> 01:40:51,389
She's still hemorrhaging.
Alice, make me a tourniquet. Your belt.

1452
01:40:51,456 --> 01:40:53,753
Carlisle, what's my other option?

1453
01:40:53,824 --> 01:40:54,950
(GASPING)

1454
01:40:55,025 --> 01:40:57,152
Tie it above my hands.

1455
01:40:57,228 --> 01:40:58,627
Carlisle!

1456
01:41:00,531 --> 01:41:01,828
Go.

1457
01:41:06,370 --> 01:41:09,203
We could try to suck the venom out.
- You know I won't be able to stop.

1458
01:41:09,273 --> 01:41:11,468
Then find the will to stop.

1459
01:41:12,409 --> 01:41:13,842
But choose.

1460
01:41:13,911 --> 01:41:16,106
She only has minutes left.

1461
01:41:18,282 --> 01:41:20,807
I'm gonna make it go away, Bella.

1462
01:41:20,884 --> 01:41:22,078
(GASPING)

1463
01:41:23,153 --> 01:41:25,178
I'm gonna make it go away.

1464
01:41:28,759 --> 01:41:30,727
(GASPING)

1465
01:41:32,830 --> 01:41:34,354
(PANTING)

1466
01:41:35,599 --> 01:41:37,122
(EDWARD GRUNTS)

1467
01:41:40,837 --> 01:41:43,237
(GRUNTS LOUDLY)

1468
01:41:43,539 --> 01:41:46,997
Edward, stop.
Her blood is clean. You're killing her.

1469
01:41:47,744 --> 01:41:49,075
Edward.

1470
01:41:49,579 --> 01:41:50,705
Stop.

1471
01:41:51,914 --> 01:41:53,074
(SOFTLY) Stop.

1472
01:41:54,651 --> 01:41:56,209
Find the will.

1473
01:41:56,286 --> 01:42:00,347
<i>(BLUESY POP BALLAD PLAYING)</i>

1474
01:42:20,776 --> 01:42:23,973
<i>BELLA: Death is peaceful, easy.</i>

1475
01:42:31,386 --> 01:42:33,115
<i>Life is harder.</i>

1476
01:42:38,593 --> 01:42:39,924
Bella?

1477
01:42:41,897 --> 01:42:43,091
Baby?

1478
01:42:44,733 --> 01:42:45,961
(WHISPERS) Bella.

1479
01:42:47,803 --> 01:42:49,236
Mom?
- Hey.

1480
01:42:49,971 --> 01:42:51,495
Where is he?

1481
01:42:51,573 --> 01:42:53,040
Where's...

1482
01:42:53,508 --> 01:42:54,998
Where's Edward?

1483
01:42:55,077 --> 01:42:56,601
He's asleep.

1484
01:42:57,779 --> 01:42:59,041
He never leaves.

1485
01:42:59,114 --> 01:43:02,139
And your dad, he's down at the cafeteria.

1486
01:43:02,650 --> 01:43:04,277
What happened?

1487
01:43:04,852 --> 01:43:07,719
Well, when you fell, you broke your leg,

1488
01:43:08,723 --> 01:43:11,248
and you lost a lot of blood.

1489
01:43:11,325 --> 01:43:14,089
You don't remember any of this, do you?

1490
01:43:15,663 --> 01:43:17,358
Edward came down with his dad

1491
01:43:17,431 --> 01:43:19,865
to try to convince you
to come back to Forks.

1492
01:43:19,934 --> 01:43:23,301
So you went over to their hotel,
then you tripped,

1493
01:43:23,371 --> 01:43:26,135
and you fell down two flights of stairs.

1494
01:43:26,807 --> 01:43:28,775
Went through a window.

1495
01:43:34,915 --> 01:43:36,780
Yeah, that sounds like me.

1496
01:43:36,851 --> 01:43:38,978
Oh, honey, I'm so sorry.

1497
01:43:40,321 --> 01:43:41,845
(PHONE VIBRATES)

1498
01:43:42,923 --> 01:43:44,412
It's Phil.

1499
01:43:44,924 --> 01:43:46,983
He's so worried about you.

1500
01:43:48,395 --> 01:43:49,794
You're texting.

1501
01:43:49,863 --> 01:43:51,694
(CHUCKLES) Finally, yeah.

1502
01:43:53,500 --> 01:43:55,593
I told him to stay down in Florida.

1503
01:43:55,668 --> 01:43:59,729
Honey, you are gonna love Jacksonville.
It's sunny every day,

1504
01:43:59,806 --> 01:44:02,604
and we found the cutest little house,
and you've got your own bathroom.

1505
01:44:02,675 --> 01:44:05,269
Mom, I still want to live in Forks.

1506
01:44:05,879 --> 01:44:07,073
What?

1507
01:44:07,514 --> 01:44:09,505
I want to live in Forks.

1508
01:44:09,883 --> 01:44:12,511
Well, okay, but we'll talk about it.

1509
01:44:13,987 --> 01:44:15,978
Do you mind getting Dad?

1510
01:44:16,689 --> 01:44:19,681
I have to talk to him. Apologize.

1511
01:44:20,293 --> 01:44:22,523
Okay, baby. I'll go get him.

1512
01:44:23,463 --> 01:44:26,295
And I'll go get a nurse, okay?
- Okay.

1513
01:44:38,110 --> 01:44:40,044
So what happened?

1514
01:44:40,112 --> 01:44:41,704
Where's James?

1515
01:44:42,848 --> 01:44:44,816
We took care of it.

1516
01:44:51,323 --> 01:44:53,951
And the woman, Victoria, she ran off.

1517
01:44:54,493 --> 01:44:56,461
